9. KEY TECHNICAL DECISIONS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

• Contract-first API: OpenAPI spec drives all type generation (Orval + Zod)
• Drizzle ORM: type-safe schema defined in lib/db, migrations via drizzle-kit
• View count: GET /api/articles/:slug auto-increments view_count in the DB
• Category colors: stored in DB, rendered as colored dots in the article filter UI
• IUCN status colors: LC=green, NT=yellow, VU=orange, EN=red, CR=dark red, EX=grey
• React Query: all data fetching uses generated hooks with proper query keys
• Framer Motion: hover lifts on cards, fade-in on page load, staggered grid animations
• Codegen fix: orval generates duplicate exports; patched with printf override in
  lib/api-spec/package.json to write a clean index.ts for api-zod


━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
10. PENDING / FUTURE WORK
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

• GitHub push — remote configured (https://github.com/Sunayana225/blogging-website-)
  Push via Replit's Version Control panel (git icon, left sidebar) or
  provide a GitHub Personal Access Token for agent-assisted push.

• Admin panel — CRUD UI for managing articles, species, and portfolio from browser
• Markdown rendering — article body currently plain text; add react-markdown for
  rich formatting (headers, bold, blockquotes, images inline)
• SEO meta tags — add react-helmet-async for per-page title/description/OG tags
• Authentication — protect admin routes (Replit Auth or Clerk)
• Image upload — replace URL strings with object storage (Replit App Storage)
• Search — full-text search across articles and species using PostgreSQL tsvector
• Pagination — articles and species lists are unpaged; add cursor-based pagination
• RSS feed — /api/feed.xml for subscribers and aggregators
• Newsletter integration — hook up to Mailchimp or Resend for actual email delivery


